---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'GeoBlue in Colombia', level: 2 },
  { id: 'why-geoblue', text: 'Why GeoBlue for Colombia', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-pricing', text: 'Plans and Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-details', text: 'Coverage Details', level: 2 },
  { id: 'best-for', text: 'Who It\'s Best For', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Health Insurance in Colombia', href: '/countries/colombia/insurance' },
  { title: 'GeoBlue Review', href: '/providers/geoblue' },
  { title: 'GeoBlue vs Cigna', href: '/compare/cigna-global-vs-geoblue' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage' },
  { key: 'price', header: 'Price (Age 35)' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Xplorer Essential', coverage: 'Core coverage', price: '$110-140/mo' },
  { plan: 'Xplorer Select', coverage: 'Enhanced coverage', price: '$140-180/mo' },
  { plan: 'Xplorer Premier', coverage: 'Comprehensive', price: '$180-230/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="GeoBlue Health Insurance in Colombia"
  description="Guide to GeoBlue international health insurance for American expats in Colombia. BCBS network access and seamless US coverage."
  headline="GeoBlue in Colombia"
  subheadline="Blue Cross Blue Shield network for American expats. Seamless coverage in Colombia and back home in the US."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/countries/colombia-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get a GeoBlue Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/providers/geoblue"
>
  <h2 id="overview">GeoBlue in Colombia</h2>
  <p>
    GeoBlue is the international arm of Blue Cross Blue Shield, making it particularly attractive for American expats in Colombia. The BCBS network access when in the US—combined with solid international coverage—creates a seamless experience for those who split time between Colombia and home.
  </p>
  <p>
    For Americans who want the comfort of a familiar brand with genuine international capabilities, GeoBlue bridges the gap effectively.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">$140-230</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Monthly (Age 35)</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">BCBS Network</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">US coverage included</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">Made for US Expats</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">American-focused</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get Your GeoBlue Colombia Quote"
    description="BCBS-backed coverage for Americans in Colombia."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/geoblue"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="why-geoblue">Why GeoBlue for Colombia</h2>
  <p>
    GeoBlue stands out for American expats in Colombia:
  </p>

  <h3>BCBS Network Access</h3>
  <p>
    When you return to the US—for visits, business, or care—you have access to the Blue Cross Blue Shield network:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Over 90% of US hospitals in-network</li>
    <li>Hundreds of thousands of providers</li>
    <li>Negotiated rates, no balance billing</li>
    <li>Familiar experience for Americans</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Designed for Americans</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>US-style customer service expectations</li>
    <li>Familiar insurance terminology and processes</li>
    <li>Support team understands American expat needs</li>
    <li>Easy coordination if you return to US permanently</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Colombia Coverage</h3>
  <p>
    GeoBlue provides solid coverage in Colombia:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Access to major Bogotá and Medellín hospitals</li>
    <li>Direct billing at many facilities</li>
    <li>Global network of vetted providers</li>
    <li>24/7 support for emergencies</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Mobile App</h3>
  <p>
    GeoBlue's app is well-regarded:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Find nearby providers anywhere in the world</li>
    <li>Digital ID card</li>
    <li>Claims submission from your phone</li>
    <li>Telehealth access</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="plans-and-pricing">Plans and Pricing</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 italic">
    Prices shown for healthy 35-year-old. Actual premiums depend on age, health history, selected coverage, and deductible.
  </p>

  <h3>Cost Factors</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Age:</strong> Main driver of premium costs</li>
    <li><strong>Plan level:</strong> Essential vs Premier</li>
    <li><strong>Deductible:</strong> Higher deductibles lower premiums</li>
    <li><strong>US coverage amount:</strong> More US coverage = higher premiums</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-3">US Coverage Included</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800">
      Unlike some international insurers that charge extra for US coverage, GeoBlue includes meaningful US coverage in all plans. For Americans who visit home regularly, this is valuable.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="coverage-details">Coverage Details</h2>

  <h3>What's Covered</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Inpatient:</strong> Hospital stays, surgery, ICU</li>
    <li><strong>Outpatient:</strong> Doctor visits, specialists, diagnostics</li>
    <li><strong>Emergency:</strong> Worldwide emergency coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Medical evacuation to US or appropriate facility</li>
    <li><strong>Prescription drugs:</strong> Covered with plan benefits</li>
    <li><strong>Telehealth:</strong> Virtual doctor visits included</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Limitations</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions: Underwriting applies</li>
    <li>Primarily designed for Americans (less suitable for other nationalities)</li>
    <li>Maternity: Waiting periods and limits apply</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="best-for">Who It's Best For</h2>

  <h3>American Digital Nomads</h3>
  <p>
    US citizens working remotely from Colombia who travel back to the US regularly. The BCBS network makes US visits seamless.
  </p>

  <h3>Expats with US Ties</h3>
  <p>
    Americans who maintain strong connections to the US—family, property, business interests—benefit from GeoBlue's dual focus.
  </p>

  <h3>Those Planning to Return</h3>
  <p>
    If you might eventually return to the US, GeoBlue provides easier transition than purely international insurers.
  </p>

  <h3>Not Ideal For</h3>
  <p>
    Non-Americans generally find better value with other international insurers. GeoBlue's US focus is wasted if you don't need US coverage.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare GeoBlue Plans for Colombia"
    description="Find the right coverage for Americans abroad."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/geoblue"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Prices and coverage details are estimates based on typical scenarios. Get a personalized quote for accurate pricing based on your age, health, and coverage needs.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
